Sorting algorithms woh algorithms hain jo data ko sorted order (ascending ya descending) mein arrange karte hain. Do aam sorting algorithms hain: Bubble Sort aur Merge Sort. 

1. **Bubble Sort**: Yeh simple sorting technique hai jo consecutive elements ko compare karte hue array ko sort karti hai. Jab tak array sorted nahi hota, yeh process chalta rahta hai. 

Example: 

```javascript
function bubbleSort(arr) {
    let n = arr.length;
    for (let i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
        for (let j = 0; j < n - i - 1; j++) {
            if (arr[j] > arr[j + 1]) {
                [arr[j], arr[j + 1]] = [arr[j + 1], arr[j]];
            }
        }
    }
    return arr;
}
``` 

2. **Merge Sort**: Yeh divide and conquer algorithm hai jo array ko do halves mein divide karti hai, phir unhe sort karke merge karti hai. 

Example: 

```javascript
function mergeSort(arr) {
    if (arr.length <= 1) return arr;
    const mid = Math.floor(arr.length / 2);
    const left = mergeSort(arr.slice(0, mid));
    const right = mergeSort(arr.slice(mid));
    return merge(left, right);
}

function merge(left, right) {
    let sortedArray = [];
    while (left.length && right.length) {
        if (left[0] < right[0]) {
            sortedArray.push(left.shift());
        } else {
            sortedArray.push(right.shift());
        }
    }
    return [...sortedArray, ...left, ...right];
}
```

