Queue ek linear data structure hai jo FIFO (First In, First Out) principle par kaam karta hai. Iska matlab hai ke jo pehle add hota hai, wahi pehle remove hota hai. Queue ko implement karne ka ek simple tareeqa yeh hai:

```javascript
class Queue {
    constructor() {
        this.items = [];
    }
    enqueue(item) {
        this.items.push(item);
    }
    dequeue() {
        return this.items.shift();
    }
}

let queue = new Queue();
queue.enqueue('A');
queue.enqueue('B');
console.log(queue.dequeue()); // Output: A
``` 
Yahan humne ek Queue class banayi hai jisme enqueue aur dequeue methods hain.

Caching ek technique hai jisme frequently accessed data ko temporarily store kiya jata hai taake agar phir se us data ki zaroorat ho, toh use dobara fetch na karna pade. Yeh performance ko behtar banata hai. Example ke liye agar aapko ek database se baar baar data lena hai, toh aap usay cache kar sakte hain. Yeh kuch is tarah se kaam karta hai:

```javascript
let cache = {};
function getData(key) {
    if (cache[key]) {
        return cache[key]; // Return cached data
    }
    let data = fetchFromDatabase(key); // Fetch from the database
    cache[key] = data; // Cache the fetched data
    return data;
}
``` 
Is code mein agar data pehle se cache mein hai, toh hum usay seedha return karte hain, warna database se naya data lete hain aur cache mein store karte hain.

