ORM ka matlab hai Object-Relational Mapping. Yeh ek technique hai jis se aap databases ke sath objects ki tarah kaam kar sakte hain. SQLAlchemy aur Prisma dono popular ORM tools hain. SQLAlchemy Python ke liye hai jabke Prisma TypeScript aur JavaScript ke liye use hota hai. Aap SQLAlchemy mein is tarah se model define karte hain:

```python
from sqlalchemy import create_engine, Column, Integer, String
from sqlalchemy.ext.declarative import declarative_base
from sqlalchemy.orm import sessionmaker

Base = declarative_base()

class User(Base):
    __tablename__ = 'users'
    id = Column(Integer, primary_key=True)
    name = Column(String)

engine = create_engine('sqlite:///mydatabase.db')
Base.metadata.create_all(engine)
session = sessionmaker(bind=engine)()
```

Prisma ka use kuch is tarah hota hai:

```javascript
