        print('Function is called!')
        func()
    return wrapper

@my_decorator
def say_hello():
    print('Hello!')

say_hello()
``` 

Is example mein, `say_hello` function ko `my_decorator` se decorate kiya gaya hai. Jab aap `say_hello()` ko call karte hain, pehle wrapper function run hota hai jo message print karta hai, phir asli function call hota hai.

