Binary search algorithm ek efficient searching technique hai jo sorted list mein use hoti hai. Is mein hum list ko half karte hain aur dekhte hain ke jo element humein chahiye wo kis side hai. Agar wo middle element se chota hai, toh hum left half ko consider karte hain, aur agar bada hai toh right half. Yeh process tab tak chalta hai jab tak humein element mil nahi jata. Yeh time complexity O(log n) hoti hai. 

Example code in Python:
```python
def binary_search(arr, target):
    left, right = 0, len(arr) - 1
    while left <= right:
        mid = (left + right) // 2
        if arr[mid] == target:
            return mid
        elif arr[mid] < target:
            left = mid + 1
        else:
            right = mid - 1
    return -1
```
Is function ko aise call karte hain: `binary_search([1, 2, 3, 4, 5], 3)`.

Data structures ke interview mein aksar kuch basic concepts aur inki implementation puchhi jati hain. Jaise ke, aap se binary tree, linked list, stack, aur queue ke baare mein pucha ja sakta hai. Aapko kisi bhi data structure ki complexity aur use-case bhi samjhana padega. Example ke liye, yahan ek simple linked list ka code hai:

```python
class Node:
    def __init__(self, data):
        self.data = data
        self.next = None

class LinkedList:
    def __init__(self):
        self.head = None

    def append(self, data):
        new_node = Node(data)
        if not self.head:
            self.head = new_node
            return
        last = self.head
        while last.next:
            last = last.next
        last.next = new_node
```

Is tarah ke sawalat aapko data structures ke basic samajhne aur unhe implement karne mein madad karte hain.

