Rate limiting is zaruri hoti hai taake API misuse na ho aur server ki performance maintain rahe. Is se hum ek limit set karte hain ke kitne requests ek user ek specific time period mein kar sakta hai. Ye cheez DoS (Denial of Service) attacks se bhi bacha sakti hai. Jaise agar hum ek function banaen jo requests ko limit kare: 

```python
from flask import Flask, request, jsonify
from flask_limiter import Limiter

app = Flask(__name__)
limiter = Limiter(app, key_func=get_remote_address)

@app.route('/api/data', methods=['GET'])
@limiter.limit('5 per minute')  # 5 requests per minute
def get_data():
    return jsonify({'data': 'This is your data'})

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run()
```

URL shortener banane ke liye, aapko backend programming ki zaroorat hogi. Python Flask framework istemal karte hue ek simple URL shortener banaya ja sakta hai. Sab se pehle, Flask ko install karein: `pip install Flask`. Phir yeh basic code likhein:

```python
from flask import Flask, request, jsonify
import string, random

app = Flask(__name{})

# Database ki tarah ek dictionary
url_dict = {}

def generate_short_url(length=6):
    characters = string.ascii_letters + string.digits
    return ''.join(random.choices(characters, k=length))

@app.route('/shorten', methods=['POST'])
def shorten_url():
    original_url = request.json['url']
    short_url = generate_short_url()
    url_dict[short_url] = original_url
    return jsonify({'short_url': short_url})

@app.route('/<short_url>', methods=['GET'])
def redirect_to_url(short_url):
    original_url = url_dict.get(short_url)
    if original_url:
        return jsonify({'url': original_url})
    return jsonify({'error': 'URL not found'}), 404

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(debug=True)
```
Is code mein, hum POST request ke zariye original URL ko receive karte hain, phir uska short version generate karte hain aur use dictionary mein store karte hain.

