JWT (JSON Web Tokens) ek standard hai jo secure information exchange ke liye use hota hai. Jab user login karta hai, server ek JWT token generate karta hai jo user ki identity ko verify karne ke liye istemal hota hai. Yeh token client ko diya jata hai aur client ise har request mein authorization ke liye bhejta hai.

JWT mein teen parts hote hain: Header, Payload, aur Signature. Header mein token ka type aur algorithm hota hai, Payload mein user ki information hoti hai, aur Signature ensure karta hai ke token genuine hai.

Code example using Node.js:

const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');

// Token generate karna
