Stack ek linear data structure hai jisme elements last-in-first-out (LIFO) order mein add aur remove hote hain. Iska matlab hai ke jo element sabse aakhir mein add hota hai, wahi pehle remove hota hai. Stack ki basic operations hain: push (element add karna), pop (element remove karna), aur peek (top element dekhna). Aayiye ek simple example dekhte hain:

```python
class Stack:
    def __init__(self):
        self.items = []

    def push(self, item):
        self.items.append(item)

    def pop(self):
        if not self.is_empty():
            return self.items.pop()
        return None

    def peek(self):
        if not self.is_empty():
            return self.items[-1]
        return None

    def is_empty(self):
        return len(self.items) == 0

# Stack ka istemal
my_stack = Stack()
my_stack.push(10)
my_stack.push(20)
print(my_stack.pop())  # Output: 20
print(my_stack.peek())  # Output: 10
```

Is example mein humne stack create kiya, elements push kiye aur unhe pop kiya.

