Event-driven architecture ek design pattern hai jahan applications events ke around design hoti hain. Iska matlab hai ke jab bhi koi event hota hai, wo ek function ya service ko trigger karta hai. Ye architecture asynchronous hota hai, iska matlab hai ke koi bhi process dusre processes ke bina wait kiye chal sakti hai.

Example ke liye, agar aapke paas ek e-commerce app hai, jab koi user order place karta hai, to ye order placement event ko trigger karega, jo ke payment service ko notify karega. Ye sab kuch is tarah se hota hai:

