Stack ek linear data structure hai jismein data ko Last In First Out (LIFO) principle ke tehat store kiya jata hai. Iska matlab hai ke jo item sabse aakhri dafa stack mein add kiya gaya hota hai, wahi sabse pehle remove hota hai. Stack functions mein 'push' (item add karna) aur 'pop' (item remove karna) shamil hain. Yeh Python mein aise implement hota hai: 

```python
class Stack:
    def __init__(self):
        self.items = []

    def push(self, item):
        self.items.append(item)

    def pop(self):
        return self.items.pop() if not self.is_empty() else None

    def is_empty(self):
        return len(self.items) == 0

stack = Stack()
stack.push(1)
stack.push(2)
print(stack.pop())  # Output: 2
```

