JWT (JSON Web Tokens) ek secure tarika hai authentication ke liye. Jab aap user ko authenticate karte hain, toh aap ek token generate karte hain jo user ki identity ko represent karta hai. Yeh token client ke paas store hota hai aur har request ke sath server ko bheja jata hai. 

JWT ka structure teen parts mein hota hai: Header, Payload aur Signature. Header mein token ki type aur algorithm hota hai. Payload mein user ki information hoti hai. Signature isko secure karta hai taake koi is token ko modify na kar sake. 

Example:

