Observer pattern ek design pattern hai jo ek subject aur uske observers ke darmiyan communication establish karta hai. Jab bhi subject ki state change hoti hai, to observers ko notify kiya jata hai. Iska istemal tab hota hai jab aapko ek object ke state ki change ko multiple objects ko inform karna ho. Yeh loosely coupled architecture ko promote karta hai. Yeh raha iska example:

```python
class Subject:
    def __init__(self):
        self._observers = []

    def attach(self, observer):
        self._observers.append(observer)

    def notify(self):
        for observer in self._observers:
            observer.update()

class Observer:
    def update(self):
        print("Observer notified!")

# Usage
subject = Subject()
observer1 = Observer()
subject.attach(observer1)
subject.notify()  # This will notify the observer
```

React ka useEffect hook ek aisa function hai jo component ke lifecycle events ke sath kaam karta hai. Ye side effects manage karne ke liye istemal hota hai, jaise data fetching, subscriptions, ya DOM updates. Iska syntax kuch is tarah hota hai:

