```javascript
fetch('https://api.example.com/data/1', {
  method: 'DELETE'
});
```

Har method ka apna maqsad hota hai aur ye RESTful APIs mein bohot important hain.

Observer pattern ek design pattern hai jo ek object ke state change hone par multiple objects ko notify karta hai. Yani agar ek object (Subject) change hota hai, toh usse related observers ko update kar diya jata hai. Iska istemal event handling ya notification systems mein hota hai. Ek simple example:

```javascript
class Subject {
  constructor() {
    this.observers = [];
  }
  addObserver(observer) {
    this.observers.push(observer);
  }
  notifyObservers(data) {
    this.observers.forEach(observer => observer.update(data));
  }
}

class Observer {
  update(data) {
    console.log('Data received: ', data);
  }
}

let subject = new Subject();
let observer1 = new Observer();
let observer2 = new Observer();

subject.addObserver(observer1);
subject.addObserver(observer2);

subject.notifyObservers('Hello Observers!');
```

Is example mein, jab `notifyObservers` call hota hai, toh sabhi registered observers ko data receive hota hai. Yeh pattern decoupling ko promote karta hai jisse code maintain karna asaan hota hai.

JWT (JSON Web Token) ek secure way hai user authentication ke liye. Jab user login karta hai, server ek token generate karta hai jo user ke saath attach hota hai. Ye token user ki identity ko verify karta hai bina database ko baar baar check karne ke. Iska structure 3 parts hota hai: Header, Payload, aur Signature. Example ke liye, agar aapko ek JWT token generate karna hai, toh aap ye code use kar sakte hain:

```javascript
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');
const user = { id: 1, username: 'example' };
const token = jwt.sign(user, 'your_secret_key', { expiresIn: '1h' });
console.log(token);
```
Is example mein, `your_secret_key` aapka secret hota hai jo token ko sign karta hai. Jab user is token ke saath request bhejta hai, server isko verify karta hai aur user ko authenticate karta hai.

Firebase ek cloud-based platform hai jo developers ko applications banane mein madad karta hai. Iski do main cheezein hain: Authentication aur Database. 

1. **Authentication**: Iska matlab hai users ko verify karna. Firebase tumhe Google, Facebook ya email se login karne ki facility deta hai. Iska istemal karne ke liye tumhe Firebase ka SDK apne project mein add karna padega. Yeh code dekho:

```javascript
import firebase from 'firebase/app';
import 'firebase/auth';

// Firebase Configuration
const firebaseConfig = {
    apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY',
    authDomain: 'YOUR_AUTH_DOMAIN',
    projectId: 'YOUR_PROJECT_ID',
};

// Firebase Initialize
firebase.initializeApp(firebaseConfig);

// User Ko Sign In Karna
firebase.auth().signInWithEmailAndPassword(email, password)
    .then((userCredential) => {
        // Signed in
