Yahan, Next.js automatically server-side rendering karega jab koi user ye page visit karega.

Mock objects testing mein aise fake objects hote hain jo real objects ki tarah behave karte hain. Inka istemal is liye hota hai taake aap kisi bhi component ki functionality ko test kar saken bina uske dependencies ke. Yeh especially unit testing mein kaam aate hain. For example, agar aapke paas ek function hai jo database se data fetch karta hai, to aap mock object use karke is function ko bina database ke test kar sakte hain. 

Example:

```python
class Database:
    def get_data(self):
        # Ye real database se data le raha hai
        pass

class MockDatabase:
    def get_data(self):
        # Ye mock data return kar raha hai
        return ['item1', 'item2']

def fetch_data(db):
    return db.get_data()

# Testing with MockObject
mock_db = MockDatabase()
result = fetch_data(mock_db)
print(result)  # Output: ['item1', 'item2']
```
Is tarah se aap asli database ki zarurat nahi hoti aur aap easily apne code ko test kar sakte hain.

ORM ka matlab hai Object-Relational Mapping. Yeh ek technique hai jisse aap apne database ke records ko Python ke objects mein convert kar sakte hain. SQLAlchemy aur Prisma dono popular ORM tools hain. 

SQLAlchemy ek Python library hai jo aapko database ke saath interact karne ki flexibility deti hai. Aap SQLAlchemy ka use karke apne database tables ko Python classes ke through represent kar sakte hain. 

```python
from sqlalchemy import create_engine, Column, Integer, String
from sqlalchemy.ext.declarative import declarative_base
from sqlalchemy.orm import sessionmaker

Base = declarative_base()

class User(Base):
    __tablename__ = 'users'
    id = Column(Integer, primary_key=True)
    name = Column(String)

engine = create_engine('sqlite:///example.db')
Base.metadata.create_all(engine)
Session = sessionmaker(bind=engine)
session = Session()
new_user = User(name='Ali')
session.add(new_user)
session.commit()
```

Prisma ek modern ORM hai jo JavaScript aur TypeScript ke liye hai. Yeh GraphQL aur REST APIs ke saath kaam karta hai. Prisma ke saath aap schema ko define karte hain aur phir automatic queries generate kar sakte hain. 

```javascript
const { PrismaClient } = require('@prisma/client');
const prisma = new PrismaClient();

async function main() {
    const newUser = await prisma.user.create({
        data: {
            name: 'Ali',
        },
    });
    console.log(newUser);
}

main();
```

Is tarah, ORM aapko database interaction ko asan aur efficient banata hai.

WebSocket ek protocol hai jo real-time communication ke liye use hota hai. Chat application banane ke liye aapko server aur client dono ki taraf WebSocket implement karna hoga. 

1. **Server Side**: Aapko Node.js ke saath WebSocket server banana hoga. Yeh ek simple server ka example hai:

```javascript
const WebSocket = require('ws');

const server = new WebSocket.Server({ port: 8080 });

server.on('connection', (socket) => {
    console.log('New client connected');

    socket.on('message', (message) => {
        console.log('Received:', message);
        // Send message to all clients
        server.clients.forEach((client) => {
            if (client.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {
                client.send(message);
            }
        });
    });
});
```

2. **Client Side**: Aapko WebSocket client banane ke liye browser ka use karna hoga:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Chat App</title>
</head>
<body>
    <input id="message" type="text" />
    <button onclick="sendMessage()">Send</button>
    <ul id="messages"></ul>
    <script>
        const socket = new WebSocket('ws://localhost:8080');

        socket.onmessage = function(event) {
            const li = document.createElement('li');
            li.textContent = event.data;
            document.getElementById('messages').appendChild(li);
        };

        function sendMessage() {
            const message = document.getElementById('message').value;
            socket.send(message);
            document.getElementById('message').value = '';
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

Is tarah aap WebSocket ka use karke real-time chat application bana sakte hain. Server messages ko receive karta hai aur unhe clients ko send karta hai.

Svelte ek modern JavaScript framework hai jo aapko interactive web applications banane mein madad karta hai. Iska khas feature ye hai ke ye compile time par kaam karta hai, yani jab aap apna code likhte hain, to Svelte usay pehle se hi optimized JavaScript mein convert kar deta hai. Ye framework reactivity ko bahut asan banata hai. Example ke liye agar aap ek simple counter bana rahe hain, to aap Svelte ka istemal is tarah kar sakte hain:

