Data structures ke interview mein kuch aam sawal hote hain jese ke: 1. Array aur Linked List mein kya farq hai? 2. Stack aur Queue ka kya concept hai? 3. Binary Tree ko kaise traverse karte hain? 

Yahan ek example hai kis tarah aap binary tree ko traverse kar sakte hain:

```javascript
class Node {
    constructor(data) {
        this.data = data;
        this.left = null;
        this.right = null;
    }
}

function inOrderTraversal(root) {
    if (root != null) {
        inOrderTraversal(root.left);
        console.log(root.data);
        inOrderTraversal(root.right);
    }
}

const root = new Node(1);
root.left = new Node(2);
root.right = new Node(3);

inOrderTraversal(root);  // Output: 2 1 3
``` 
Is code mein, humne ek binary tree banaya hai aur usay in-order traversal ki madad se traverse kiya hai.

Next.js ek React framework hai jo server-side rendering aur static site generation ko support karta hai. Ye React ka ek extension hai jo efficiency aur performance enhance karta hai. 

React ko aap sirf client-side rendering ke liye use karte hain, lekin Next.js server-side rendering ko bhi support karta hai. Iska matlab ye hai ke aapke pages server par generate hote hain pehle, phir user ko bheje jate hain. Is se SEO mein behter madad milti hai. 

Kuch key features jo Next.js ko React se alag banate hain: 

1. **Automatic Code Splitting**: Next.js aapke pages ke liye automatically code split karta hai, is se loading time tezi se hota hai.

2. **Server-side Rendering (SSR)**: Next.js ki madad se aap apne components ko server par render kar sakte hain. 
   ```javascript
   // Example of SSR in Next.js
   export async function getServerSideProps() {
       const res = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data');
       const data = await res.json();
       return { props: { data } };
   }
   ```

3. **Static Site Generation (SSG)**: Ye feature aapko static HTML pages generate karne ki bhi ijazat deta hai. 
   ```javascript
   // Example of SSG in Next.js
   export async function getStaticProps() {
       const res = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data');
       const data = await res.json();
       return { props: { data } };
   }
   ```

In sab features ki wajah se Next.js bohot powerful hota hai jab aapko performance aur SEO ki zaroorat hoti hai.

Data structures ke interview mein aksar kuch common sawal pooche jate hain. Jaise ke, 'Array aur Linked List mein kya farq hai?' Ya phir 'Stack aur Queue kya hote hain?'. Aapko yeh concepts samajhna bohot zaroori hai. 

Ek example ke tor par, yeh hai stack ka implementation in Python:
```python
class Stack:
    def __init__(self):
        self.items = []

    def push(self, item):
        self.items.append(item)

    def pop(self):
        return self.items.pop() if not self.is_empty() else 'Stack is empty'

    def is_empty(self):
        return len(self.items) == 0
```

Data structures ke interview mein aksar basic concepts puchhe jate hain, jaise ke arrays, linked lists, stacks, aur queues. Aapko yeh bhi pata hona chahiye ke inki time complexity kya hai. Misal ke taur par, agar aapko stack implement karna hai, toh aap yeh code dekh sakte hain:

```python
class Stack:
    def __init__(self):
        self.items = []

    def push(self, item):
        self.items.append(item)

    def pop(self):
        if not self.is_empty():
            return self.items.pop()

    def is_empty(self):
        return len(self.items) == 0

    def peek(self):
        if not self.is_empty():
            return self.items[-1]
```

Is code mein humne stack ki basic functionalities implement ki hain. Aap yeh padh kar interview mein behtar tayyari kar sakte hain.

JWT (JSON Web Token) ek standard hai jise authentication aur information exchange ke liye use kiya jata hai. Jab aap user ko authenticate karte hain, toh aap unhein ek token dete hain jisse wo apne requests mein bhejte hain. Is tarah server ko pata hota hai ke user authenticated hai. Aap JWT generate karne ke liye 'jsonwebtoken' library ka istemal kar sakte hain. Yahan ek example hai:

```javascript
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');

// Secret key for signing the token
const secretKey = 'your_secret_key';

// Function to generate token
function generateToken(user) {
    const token = jwt.sign({ id: user.id }, secretKey, { expiresIn: '1h' });
    return token;
}

// Example of a user object
const user = { id: 1, username: 'example_user' };
const token = generateToken(user);
console.log(token);
```

Is code mein humne ek simple function banaya hai jo user object ko le kar JWT token generate karta hai. Yeh token aap authentication ke liye use kar sakte hain.

