ORM ka matlab hai Object-Relational Mapping. Yeh ek technique hai jisse hum databases ko objects ke zariye access kar sakte hain. Matlab, hum SQL queries likhne ki bajaye objects ke sath kaam karte hain jo keh programming language ke objects hote hain. 

SQLAlchemy ek popular ORM hai Python ke liye, jabke Prisma JavaScript/TypeScript ke liye use hota hai. 

Example for SQLAlchemy:
```python
from sqlalchemy import create_engine, Column, Integer, String
from sqlalchemy.ext.declarative import declarative_base
from sqlalchemy.orm import sessionmaker

Base = declarative_base()

class User(Base):
    __tablename__ = 'users'
    id = Column(Integer, primary_key=True)
    name = Column(String)

engine = create_engine('sqlite:///:memory:')
Base.metadata.create_all(engine)
Session = sessionmaker(bind=engine)
session = Session()

new_user = User(name='Ali')
session.add(new_user)
session.commit()
``` 

Example for Prisma:
```javascript
// Prisma schema.prisma file
model User {
  id    Int     @id @default(autoincrement())
  name  String
}

// Using Prisma Client
async function main() {
  const newUser = await prisma.user.create({
    data: { name: 'Ali' },
  });
  console.log(newUser);
}
main();
```

