JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication ek secure tareeqa hai user ki identity ko verify karne ka. Jab user login karta hai, server ek token generate karta hai jo user ki information rakhta hai. Ye token client ko diya jata hai aur agle requests mein ye token use hota hai. Iska format kuch aisa hota hai: 

```javascript
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');

// User login ke baad token generate karna
const token = jwt.sign({ userId: user.id }, 'secretKey', { expiresIn: '1h' });

// Token ko verify karna
jwt.verify(token, 'secretKey', (err, decoded) => {
  if (err) {
    return res.status(401).send('Invalid token');
  }
  // User authenticated
});
``` 

Ye token client side par store hota hai (jaise localStorage ya cookies) aur har request mein isay include kiya jata hai.

