Redux aur Context API dono state management ke liye istemal hotay hain, lekin inka istemal mukhtalif scenarios mein hota hai. Redux zyada complex applications ke liye behtar hota hai, jahan state management zyada centralized aur predictable honi chahiye. Isme aapko actions aur reducers define karne hote hain. Misal ke taur par:

```javascript
import { createStore } from 'redux';

const initialState = { count: 0 };

const counterReducer = (state = initialState, action) => {
    switch (action.type) {
        case 'INCREMENT':
            return { ...state, count: state.count + 1 };
        default:
            return state;
    }
};

const store = createStore(counterReducer);
```

Dusri taraf, Context API simpler hai aur choti applications ke liye behtar hai. Yeh ek global state provide karta hai bina prop drilling ke. Misal ke taur par:

```javascript
import React, { createContext, useContext, useState } from 'react';

const CountContext = createContext();

const CountProvider = ({ children }) => {
    const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
    return (
        <CountContext.Provider value={{ count, setCount }}>
            {children}
        </CountContext.Provider>
    );
};

const Counter = () => {
    const { count, setCount } = useContext(CountContext);
    return <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>Count: {count}</button>;
};
```

In dono tools ka istemal aapki application ki complexity aur requirements par depend karta hai.

