Queue ek linear data structure hai jo First In First Out (FIFO) principle par kaam karta hai. Iska matlab hai ke jo element pehle aata hai, wahi pehle nikalta hai. Queue ko implement karne ke liye aap arrays ya linked lists ka istemal kar sakte hain. Yahan ek simple example hai Python mein:

```python
class Queue:
    def __init__(self):
        self.items = []

    def is_empty(self):
        return len(self.items) == 0

    def enqueue(self, item):
        self.items.insert(0, item)  # add item to the front

    def dequeue(self):
        return self.items.pop()  # remove item from the back

    def peek(self):
        return self.items[-1]  # return the last item

    def size(self):
        return len(self.items)

# Queue ka istemal
queue = Queue()
queue.enqueue(1)
queue.enqueue(2)
print(queue.dequeue())  # Output: 1
```

Is example mein, humne queue ko define kiya hai aur enqueue aur dequeue operations implement kiye hain. Aap is code ko apne local machine par run karke dekh sakte hain!

