Data Structures ke interview questions aksar aise hote hain jo aapke problem-solving skills ko test karte hain. Yahan kuch common questions hain: 

1. **Array aur Linked List mein kya farq hai?** 
   Array mein contiguous memory allocation hoti hai jabki Linked List mein nodes ek doosre se linked hote hain. Ye farq unki performance aur memory management par asar daal sakta hai.

2. **Stack aur Queue ka kya maqsad hai?**  
   Stack Last In First Out (LIFO) principle par kaam karta hai jabki Queue First In First Out (FIFO) principle par.

3. **Binary Tree kya hota hai?**  
   Binary Tree ek aisa data structure hai jisme har node ke sirf do children hote hain. Aap isko traversal ke techniques jaise Inorder, Preorder, aur Postorder se access kar sakte hain. 

4. **Kya aap mujhe example de sakte hain Binary Search Tree ka?**  
   Binary Search Tree (BST) ek special type ka binary tree hai jahan left child node hamesha parent node se chhota hota hai aur right child node bada. Example:

   ```javascript
   class Node {
     constructor(data) {
       this.left = null;
       this.right = null;
       this.data = data;
     }
   }

   class BinarySearchTree {
     constructor() {
       this.root = null;
     }

     insert(data) {
       const newNode = new Node(data);
       if (this.root === null) {
         this.root = newNode;
       } else {
         this.insertNode(this.root, newNode);
       }
     }

     insertNode(node, newNode) {
       if (newNode.data < node.data) {
         if (node.left === null) {
           node.left = newNode;
         } else {
           this.insertNode(node.left, newNode);
         }
       } else {
         if (node.right === null) {
           node.right = newNode;
         } else {
           this.insertNode(node.right, newNode);
         }
       }
     }
   }
   ```

Yeh kuch basic questions hain jo aapko Data Structures interviews mein puchhe ja sakte hain.

