Redux aur Context API dono state management ke liye use hote hain, lekin inka istemal mukhtalif scenarios mein hota hai. Redux zyada complex applications ke liye acha hai jahan aapko ek centralized store ki zaroorat hoti hai. Ismein aap actions aur reducers ka istemal karte hain. Context API choti applications ya components ke liye behtar hai jahan aapko sirf simple state sharing ki zaroorat hoti hai. 

Example: Redux ka istemal karte waqt aap aise code likhte hain:

```javascript
import { createStore } from 'redux';

const initialState = { count: 0 };  
const reducer = (state = initialState, action) => {
  switch (action.type) {
    case 'INCREMENT':
      return { count: state.count + 1 };
    default:
      return state;
  }
};

const store = createStore(reducer);
```

Aur agar aap Context API istemal karte hain:

```javascript
import React, { createContext, useContext, useState } from 'react';
const MyContext = createContext();

const MyProvider = ({ children }) => {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  return (
    <MyContext.Provider value={{ count, setCount }}>
      {children}
    </MyContext.Provider>
  );
};

const MyComponent = () => {
  const { count, setCount } = useContext(MyContext);
  return <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>{count}</button>;
};
```

Toh, agar aapki application complex hai, toh Redux use karein, warna Context API kaafi hai.

