Great question! WebSocket aur HTTP dono protocols hain lekin inka istemal mukhtalif scenarios mein hota hai. 

- **HTTP**: Yeh request-response model par kaam karta hai. Client server ko request bhejta hai aur server uska response deta hai. Yeh stateless hai, matlab har request independent hoti hai. Yeh web pages ko load karne aur API calls ke liye use hota hai. 

- **WebSocket**: Yeh bi-directional communication establish karta hai. Iska matlab yeh hai ke ek baar connection ho jaye to client aur server dono asaani se messages exchange kar sakte hain bina naye requests bheje. Yeh real-time applications jese chat apps ya live notifications ke liye behtareen hai. 

Ek chhota sa code example:

```javascript
// HTTP request using Fetch API
