Bubble sort ek simple sorting algorithm hai jo list ko iteratively traverse karta hai aur adjacent elements ko compare karke swap karta hai agar wo galat order mein hain. Yeh process tab tak chalta hai jab tak complete list sorted na ho jaye. Iska basic code kuch is tarah hai:

```python
def bubble_sort(arr):
    n = len(arr)
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(0, n-i-1):
            if arr[j] > arr[j+1]:
                arr[j], arr[j+1] = arr[j+1], arr[j]
    return arr

example_list = [64, 34, 25, 12, 22, 11, 90]
sorted_list = bubble_sort(example_list)
print(sorted_list)  # Output: [11, 12, 22, 25, 34, 64, 90]
```

