```  

Is tarah se aap search functionality asaani se add kar sakte hain!

ORM ka matlab hai Object-Relational Mapping. Ye aik technique hai jisse hum apne database tables ko objects ke through represent kar sakte hain. SQLAlchemy aur Prisma do mashhoor ORM tools hain. SQLAlchemy Python ke liye hai aur Prisma JavaScript/TypeScript ke liye. 

Example SQLAlchemy ka:
```python
from sqlalchemy import create_engine, Column, Integer, String
from sqlalchemy.ext.declarative import declarative_base
from sqlalchemy.orm import sessionmaker

Base = declarative_base()

class User(Base):
    __tablename__ = 'users'
    id = Column(Integer, primary_key=True)
    name = Column(String)

engine = create_engine('sqlite:///:memory:')
Base.metadata.create_all(engine)
Session = sessionmaker(bind=engine)
session = Session()

new_user = User(name='Ali')
session.add(new_user)
session.commit()
```

Example Prisma ka:
```javascript
// prisma.schema
model User {
  id    Int    @id @default(autoincrement())
  name  String
}

// JavaScript code
const { PrismaClient } = require('@prisma/client');
const prisma = new PrismaClient();

async function main() {
  const newUser = await prisma.user.create({
    data: { name: 'Ali' },
  });
  console.log(newUser);
}
main();
```

CORS ka matlab hai Cross-Origin Resource Sharing. Ye ek security feature hai jo browser ko allow karta hai ke woh ek domain se doosre domain mein resources share kare. Agar aapka frontend aur backend alag domains par hain, to aapko CORS error face karna par sakta hai. 

CORS error tab aata hai jab aapka web application ek server se request karta hai jo CORS ko allow nahi karta. Isko fix karne ke liye apne backend server par CORS headers set karne hote hain. 

Agar aap Flask use karte hain to aap `flask-cors` library istemal kar sakte hain: 

Example: 
```python
from flask import Flask
from flask_cors import CORS

app = Flask(__name__)
CORS(app)  # Yeh line CORS ko enable karti hai

@app.route('/data')
def data():
    return {'message': 'Hello from the server!'}

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run()
``` 

Agar aap Express.js use karte hain to aap `cors` middleware istemal kar sakte hain: 

Example: 
```javascript
const express = require('express');
const cors = require('cors');

const app = express();
app.use(cors());  // CORS ko enable karta hai

app.get('/data', (req, res) => {
    res.json({ message: 'Hello from the server!' });
});

app.listen(3000, () => {
    console.log('Server running on port 3000');
});
```

Event-driven architecture ek design pattern hai jisme applications events par react karte hain. Isme components ek doosre se loosely coupled hote hain, yani agar ek component change hota hai to dusre components par asar nahi hota. Iska fayda ye hai ke aap asani se system ko scale kar sakte hain aur naye features add kar sakte hain without affecting existing functionality. Ek simple example ke liye, agar aap ek messaging application bana rahe hain to jab koi user message bhejta hai, ek event generate hota hai jo doosre components ko notify karta hai ke naya message aya hai. Iska code kuch is tarah ho sakta hai:

```javascript
const sendMessage = (message) => {
    // Event generate karna
    const event = new Event('messageSent');
    document.dispatchEvent(event);
};

document.addEventListener('messageSent', () => {
    console.log('Naya message aya!');
});

sendMessage('Hello!');
```

React me useState hook aapko functional components me state manage karne ki ijazat deta hai. Ye ek array return karta hai jisme pehla element current state hota hai aur doosra element state update karne ka function hota hai. Iska use karke aap easily component ki state ko update kar sakte hain. Ek simple example dekhein:

```javascript
import React, { useState } from 'react';

const Counter = () => {
    const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

    return (
        <div>
            <p>Count: {count}</p>
            <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>Increment</button>
        </div>
    );
};

export default Counter;
``` 
Is example me, jab aap button par click karte hain, count ki value increment hoti hai aur component re-render hota hai.

