}

main();
```

Is tarah se ORM aapke liye database ke sath kaam karna asan bana deta hai.

WebSocket aur HTTP dono protocols hain lekin inke beech kuch key differences hain. HTTP ek request-response protocol hai jahan client server ko request bhejta hai aur server response karta hai. Lekin WebSocket ek full-duplex communication protocol hai jahan client aur server dono ek hi connection pe ek dusre se real-time data exchange kar sakte hain. Iska matlab hai ki WebSocket use karne se aapko latency kam hoti hai aur aap bina naye request bheje real-time notifications ya updates receive kar sakte hain. Yahan ek chhota sa example hai WebSocket server ka: 

```javascript
const WebSocket = require('ws');
const server = new WebSocket.Server({ port: 8080 });

server.on('connection', socket => {
