Event-driven architecture ek aisi design pattern hai jahan system events par react karta hai. Yani jab koi event hota hai, to woh ek ya zyada functions ya services ko trigger karta hai. Iska faida ye hai ke ye loosely coupled hota hai, jis se scalability aur maintenance aasan hota hai. Misal ke taur par, agar aapke paas ek order service hai jo order complete hone par notification bhejti hai, to aap event emit karte hain jab order complete hota hai.

Example in JavaScript:

```javascript
