Binary search ek efficient search algorithm hai jo sorted array ya list mein kisi element ko search karne ke liye istemal hota hai. Yeh algorithm half division ka istemal karta hai. Sab se pehle, aapko list ko sort karna hoga. Phir aap middle element ko check karte hain. Agar wo element dhoondh raha element se chhota hai, toh aap search ko right half par continue karte hain. Agar wo bada hai, toh aap left half par search continue karte hain. Yeh process tab tak chalta hai jab tak element mil nahi jata ya list khatam nahi ho jati. Yahan ek example hai:

```python
def binary_search(arr, x):
    left, right = 0, len(arr) - 1
    while left <= right:
        mid = left + (right - left) // 2
        if arr[mid] == x:
            return mid
        elif arr[mid] < x:
            left = mid + 1
        else:
            right = mid - 1
    return -1

# Example usage:
arr = [2, 3, 4, 10, 40]
x = 10
result = binary_search(arr, x)
if result != -1:
    print('Element found at index', result)
else:
    print('Element not found')
```

