Binary search ek efficient searching algorithm hai jo sorted arrays mein istemal hota hai. Iska kaam yeh hai ke woh array ko half karta hai aur dekhta hai ke target value kis side mein hai (left ya right). Agar value mil jati hai, toh woh index return karta hai, warna yeh process continue rehta hai jab tak value nahi mil jaati ya array khatam nahi ho jata.

Yahan ek simple example hai:

```python
def binary_search(arr, target):
    left, right = 0, len(arr) - 1
    while left <= right:
        mid = (left + right) // 2
        if arr[mid] == target:
            return mid  # target found
        elif arr[mid] < target:
            left = mid + 1  # search in the right half
        else:
            right = mid - 1  # search in the left half
    return -1  # target not found
```

Is function ko aap ek sorted array aur target value dete hain, aur agar value milti hai toh index return hota hai, nahi toh -1 milta hai.

