Stack ek linear data structure hai jo Last In First Out (LIFO) principle par kaam karta hai. Iska matlab hai ke jo element sabse pehle bilkul last mein aata hai, wahi sabse pehle nikalta hai. Stack ko implement karne ka ek example dekhein:

```python
class Stack:
    def __init__(self):
        self.items = []

    def is_empty(self):
        return len(self.items) == 0

    def push(self, item):
        self.items.append(item)

    def pop(self):
        return self.items.pop() if not self.is_empty() else None

    def peek(self):
        return self.items[-1] if not self.is_empty() else None

    def size(self):
        return len(self.items)

# Stack ka istemal
my_stack = Stack()
my_stack.push(1)
my_stack.push(2)
my_stack.push(3)
print(my_stack.pop())  # Output: 3
print(my_stack.peek())  # Output: 2
```

Is example mein, humne ek simple Stack class banayi hai jisme push, pop aur peek operations hain.

